reviews.reviewText: I was pleasantly surprised with this purchase. Literally just about every basic kitchen utensil you could need. The quality was great for the price. My only complaints are 1. the pizza cutter was very flimsy 2. the rubber ends are great but they attract dust and fuzzies which cant be wiped off easily. I still love the set and i’m glad I found it. This would definitely be great for anyone starting out in a new place or someone just looking to replace their utensils on a budget. Additionally, the holder for the utensils is a little smaller than I imagined and hoped, but it still fits everything I need it to hold from the set and won’t tip over.

The high-quality materials not only make them durable but also safe to use on my nonstick cookware. I appreciate the attention to detail in design – the ergonomic handles provide a comfortable grip, making it a breeze to maneuver in the kitchen.What sets this set apart is the versatility of the utensils. From spatulas to ladles and everything in between, it has every tool I need for various cooking tasks. The silicone construction ensures that I can confidently use them on my nonstick pans without worrying about scratches.The vibrant colors add a fun touch to my kitchen, and the easy-to-clean design makes post-cooking cleanup a breeze. The inclusion of 33 kitchen tools in one set is a fantastic value for the price.Overall, I highly recommend this Kitchen Utensil Set to anyone looking to upgrade their cooking tools. It's a complete package that combines style, functionality, and durability – a must-have for every kitchen!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 15, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I understand that there are cheap alternatives to certain necessities and whatever that is, is expected to not be as durable or sturdy, but it baffles me that there are entire manufacturer warehouses that build these certain things knowing how unreliable they are. What's the point of creating something that doesn't hold up? At least for a while? I've had this set for about a month. The can opener worked for like once and is completely useless, the ice cream scoop is as flimsy as a spoon, the utensil holder is very light and can easily be tipped over due to how tall some of the utensils are , and the whisk wires are not driven through the whole handle. In fact, they're very short and already starting to come out.Granted, you do get a lot out of this set and the main cooking utensils (Spatula, stirring spoon, tongs, ladle) hold up pretty well.At the end of the day, I expect for whatever I pay for to do its job for a reasonable amount of time
